Cultivate joy in your family, young ones, rejoice in your parents.

00:57:56.769 --> 00:58:09.650
This symposium has helped us to appreciate even more Jehovah's love for families.

00:58:09.650 --> 00:58:12.650
And we appreciate this gift, the Bible,

00:58:12.650 --> 00:58:20.650
which could serve as a blueprint for families to have a loving, warm, safe environment.

00:58:20.650 --> 00:58:27.650
And you, young ones, you play a vital role in contributing to the joy in your family life.

00:58:27.650 --> 00:58:31.650
Your mother, your father, they love you very much.

00:58:31.650 --> 00:58:36.650
And they want to have a close, personal, loving relationship with you.

00:58:36.650 --> 00:58:43.650
And it's their heartfelt desire that you have a close, personal, loving relationship

00:58:43.650 --> 00:58:45.650
with your Heavenly Father, Jehovah.

00:58:45.650 --> 00:58:52.650
They want you to be happy now and for the rest of your life, everlasting life.

00:58:52.650 --> 00:58:59.650
In the previous talk, we understood how Jehovah wants parents to train their children.

00:58:59.650 --> 00:59:01.650
But with what purpose?

00:59:01.650 --> 00:59:09.650
Notice what Proverbs chapter 22 and verse 6 gives us instructions for parents.

00:59:09.650 --> 00:59:12.650
They're in verse 6, it reads,

00:59:12.650 --> 00:59:19.650
train a boy, or the footnote says, child or youth, in the way he should go.

00:59:19.650 --> 00:59:24.650
Even when he grows old, he will not depart from it.

00:59:24.650 --> 00:59:28.650
So what is Jehovah asking of your parents?

00:59:28.650 --> 00:59:30.650
To train you.

00:59:30.650 --> 00:59:38.650
To train you in such a way that you will always serve Jehovah from your youth all the way to your adulthood.

00:59:38.650 --> 00:59:41.650
And really, for the rest of your life.

00:59:41.650 --> 00:59:49.650
So Jehovah doesn't spell out every single detail for parents on how they should instruct you and how they should train you.

00:59:49.650 --> 00:59:51.650
That's left up to them.

00:59:51.650 --> 00:59:57.650
And so they need to prayerfully think about what would be best for your family and for you as a child.

00:59:57.650 --> 00:59:59.650
Personally.

00:59:59.650 --> 01:00:02.650
This means that they will make house rules.

01:00:02.650 --> 01:00:06.650
Sometimes you'll get chores, maybe curfews.

01:00:06.650 --> 01:00:09.650
You will get reminders, correction and discipline.

01:00:09.650 --> 01:00:11.650
Why?

01:00:11.650 --> 01:00:13.650
Because they love you.

01:00:13.650 --> 01:00:17.650
And because they're doing their best to listen and obey Jehovah.

01:00:17.650 --> 01:00:25.650
And his instructions are to train you, discipline you, so you can serve Jehovah forever.

01:00:25.650 --> 01:00:27.650
It's not an easy assignment.

01:00:27.650 --> 01:00:33.650
They need all the help that they can get from Jehovah as well as from you.

01:00:33.650 --> 01:00:36.650
Especially when they make rules that you may not like.

01:00:36.650 --> 01:00:39.650
What you can and cannot wear.

01:00:39.650 --> 01:00:41.650
What you can and cannot listen to or watch.

01:00:41.650 --> 01:00:44.650
Or who you pick as close friends.

01:00:44.650 --> 01:00:47.650
These are decisions that are left to your parents.

01:00:47.650 --> 01:00:52.650
Now will your parents always make the perfect decision, the perfect rule?

01:00:52.650 --> 01:00:53.650
No.

01:00:53.650 --> 01:00:55.650
Breaking news.

01:00:55.650 --> 01:00:59.650
It's not news to you that they will make mistakes.

01:00:59.650 --> 01:01:01.650
They're imperfect.

01:01:01.650 --> 01:01:07.650
But they love you and they're doing the best they can to give you the best training possible.

01:01:07.650 --> 01:01:11.650
So you can love Jehovah and serve him forever.

01:01:11.650 --> 01:01:16.650
We know that you love and appreciate all that your parents do for you.

01:01:16.650 --> 01:01:18.650
But let's be real.

01:01:18.650 --> 01:01:22.650
Sometimes you don't understand the reason for the rule.

01:01:22.650 --> 01:01:25.650
Or you simply don't agree with it.

01:01:25.650 --> 01:01:26.650
What do you do?

01:01:26.650 --> 01:01:28.650
Well, you get frustrated.

01:01:28.650 --> 01:01:30.650
But that's okay.

01:01:30.650 --> 01:01:31.650
We've been there.

01:01:31.650 --> 01:01:36.650
We were your age at one time and we completely understand that it could be frustrating.

01:01:36.650 --> 01:01:41.650
But we know that this will pass because you'll understand why they're doing this.

01:01:41.650 --> 01:01:43.650
It's out of love.

01:01:43.650 --> 01:01:49.650
So when you don't see eye to eye, what are you supposed to do?

01:01:49.650 --> 01:01:52.650
Sometimes you need to change your view.

01:01:52.650 --> 01:01:57.650
A much has to do with how you view your parents.

01:01:57.650 --> 01:02:05.650
How you view your mother and your father will affect how much or how little you respect them.

01:02:05.650 --> 01:02:09.650
Listen to them and obey them.

01:02:09.650 --> 01:02:12.650
And here's a question we'd like to pose to you children.

01:02:12.650 --> 01:02:20.650
Do you sometimes view your parents as prison guards or lifeguards?

01:02:20.650 --> 01:02:22.650
Interesting question.

01:02:22.650 --> 01:02:28.650
Prison guards are trained to keep a close watch over prisoners because they don't really trust them.

01:02:28.650 --> 01:02:32.650
They keep them confined with many restrictions.

01:02:32.650 --> 01:02:35.650
They tell them what to do and when to do it.

01:02:35.650 --> 01:02:38.650
When to get up and when to go to sleep.

01:02:38.650 --> 01:02:41.650
What they will eat and when they will eat.

01:02:41.650 --> 01:02:44.650
What they will wear and all kinds of other rules.

01:02:44.650 --> 01:02:48.650
They keep all these restrictions because they don't trust them.

01:02:48.650 --> 01:02:53.650
Do you view your parents as prison guards at times?

01:02:53.650 --> 01:02:58.650
Well, you might, especially if you want more freedom, more independence.

01:02:58.650 --> 01:03:04.650
And if it seems like they don't really trust you, they're watching every single move that you make.

01:03:04.650 --> 01:03:09.650
You might feel confined because of all the rules and restrictions.

01:03:09.650 --> 01:03:12.650
What about lifeguards?

01:03:12.650 --> 01:03:14.650
Well, lifeguards also watch people.

01:03:14.650 --> 01:03:17.650
They watch swimmers but for a very different reason.

01:03:17.650 --> 01:03:19.650
They want to keep them safe.

01:03:19.650 --> 01:03:22.650
They want to make sure that they do not swim into danger.

01:03:22.650 --> 01:03:27.650
So from their lifeguard tower, they keep a close watch over all the swimmers.

01:03:27.650 --> 01:03:31.650
Sometimes they will use their whistle to warn you of danger.

01:03:31.650 --> 01:03:37.650
To keep away from riptides or maybe sharks, things that you're not aware of.

01:03:37.650 --> 01:03:41.650
Do you view your parents as lifeguards?

01:03:41.650 --> 01:03:44.650
We hope so because they are.

01:03:44.650 --> 01:03:49.650
It's been said that you could spend years wishing your parents would get off your back

01:03:49.650 --> 01:03:55.650
only to realize that they're the only ones who ever really had your back.

01:03:55.650 --> 01:04:00.650
Yes, your parents like lifeguards are looking out for your best interest.

01:04:00.650 --> 01:04:05.650
They've always had your back and they always will.

01:04:05.650 --> 01:04:11.650
They want to make sure that you avoid being drawn into the dangerous currents in this wicked world.

01:04:11.650 --> 01:04:15.650
Dangerous that you may not be aware of.

01:04:15.650 --> 01:04:18.650
Do you want to be happier?

01:04:18.650 --> 01:04:21.650
Do you want to have more trust from your parents?

01:04:21.650 --> 01:04:23.650
More freedom, more independence?

01:04:23.650 --> 01:04:28.650
If so, you might have to change your view of your parents.

01:04:28.650 --> 01:04:32.650
And don't view them in a negative way like their prison guards,

01:04:32.650 --> 01:04:38.650
but view them like lifeguards, safe guarding your life.

01:04:38.650 --> 01:04:44.650
Your parents love you very much and their training will pay off if you listen.

01:04:44.650 --> 01:04:47.650
And that's what Jehovah is asking you to do.

01:04:47.650 --> 01:04:52.650
While your parents are training you, you need to do your part and that is listen.

01:04:52.650 --> 01:04:59.650
And that's what our scripture at Proverbs chapter 23 has for an assignment for you.

01:04:59.650 --> 01:05:04.650
That's chapter 23 of Proverbs in verse 22.

01:05:04.650 --> 01:05:11.650
And their verse 22 says to your children, listen to your father who caused your birth

01:05:11.650 --> 01:05:18.650
and do not despise or dislike your mother just because she has grown old.

01:05:18.650 --> 01:05:24.650
So, although it's not easy at times, what is Jehovah asking of you?

01:05:24.650 --> 01:05:29.650
As your parents are training you, please listen to them.

01:05:29.650 --> 01:05:32.650
But what does it mean to listen?

01:05:32.650 --> 01:05:35.650
Listen is more than just hearing words.

01:05:35.650 --> 01:05:40.650
It's hearing with a view to obey.

01:05:40.650 --> 01:05:46.650
Listening to your mother and your father means giving them your full attention,

01:05:46.650 --> 01:05:49.650
divided attention.

01:05:49.650 --> 01:05:54.650
It means turning off your music, taking out your earbuds,

01:05:54.650 --> 01:06:01.650
putting away your phone and avoiding rolling your eyes when they're speaking to you.

01:06:01.650 --> 01:06:05.650
At times you may get frustrated, you may get upset.

01:06:05.650 --> 01:06:08.650
That's understandable. We all do.

01:06:08.650 --> 01:06:14.650
But how you control your emotions will affect the outcome in the future.

01:06:14.650 --> 01:06:20.650
By listening and obeying your parents, you are building a record of trust

01:06:20.650 --> 01:06:24.650
that will help you in the future when you need to communicate with them.

01:06:24.650 --> 01:06:26.650
Maybe about rules.

01:06:26.650 --> 01:06:30.650
Remember, trust is something that you earn.

01:06:30.650 --> 01:06:35.650
It's not something that you demand or that's automatic.

01:06:35.650 --> 01:06:41.650
What is the best way for you to speak to your parents about rules that you don't understand

01:06:41.650 --> 01:06:44.650
or maybe that you don't agree with?

01:06:44.650 --> 01:06:46.650
You need to communicate.

01:06:46.650 --> 01:06:49.650
Good, open communication.

01:06:49.650 --> 01:06:55.650
Communication doesn't mean complaining, shouting, whining.

01:06:55.650 --> 01:06:58.650
Maybe replying with sarcasm.

01:06:58.650 --> 01:07:00.650
It means calmly.

01:07:00.650 --> 01:07:03.650
Tell your parents how you feel.

01:07:03.650 --> 01:07:06.650
Tell them what's on your mind.

01:07:06.650 --> 01:07:10.650
The following Bible verse helps if we can apply it.

01:07:10.650 --> 01:07:15.650
Verse 29-11 says, a stupid person gives vent to all his feelings.

01:07:15.650 --> 01:07:17.650
It's out of control. No control.

01:07:17.650 --> 01:07:22.650
But the wise one calmly keeps them in check.

01:07:22.650 --> 01:07:24.650
In control.

01:07:24.650 --> 01:07:27.650
That's what we want to try to follow.

01:07:27.650 --> 01:07:31.650
A young woman named Devon tried to do this and this is what she advises.

01:07:31.650 --> 01:07:37.650
She says, I found that when I stayed calm and presented my thoughts clearly,

01:07:37.650 --> 01:07:42.650
I could counter my parents to listen and either to reason with me on their decision

01:07:42.650 --> 01:07:46.650
or to come up with another solution.

01:07:46.650 --> 01:07:50.650
Parents appreciate having a real conversation with their children

01:07:50.650 --> 01:07:55.650
rather than screaming matches that end up with slamming doors.

01:07:55.650 --> 01:07:58.650
Open communication is what's needed.

01:07:58.650 --> 01:08:02.650
So you, young ones, what have we learned?

01:08:02.650 --> 01:08:05.650
We have learned how to view our parents correctly.

01:08:05.650 --> 01:08:11.650
Not as a prison guard, but as a lifeguard who really wants to save your life.

01:08:11.650 --> 01:08:13.650
You're everlasting life.

01:08:13.650 --> 01:08:16.649
They have your back and they always will.

01:08:16.649 --> 01:08:20.649
Listening and obeying strengthens your relationship with your parents

01:08:20.649 --> 01:08:23.649
as well as your Heavenly Father, Jehovah.

01:08:23.649 --> 01:08:27.649
It brings you joy and brings joy to your parents.

01:08:27.649 --> 01:08:31.649
And as you apply the training that your parents are giving to you,

01:08:31.649 --> 01:08:36.649
you will gain wisdom that will help you now to make wise decisions

01:08:36.649 --> 01:08:39.649
so that you can have their real life.

01:08:39.649 --> 01:08:42.649
Yes, everlasting life.

01:08:42.649 --> 01:08:46.649
As you watch the concluding video of this symposium,

01:08:46.649 --> 01:08:52.649
please notice how these children find joy in their parents.

